Dubai - DWC (DWC), United Arab EmiratesTravel Required:
up to 75%The Panalpina Group is one of the world's leading providers of supply chain solutions, combining its core products of Air Freight, Ocean Freight, and Logistics to deliver globally integrated, tailor-made end-to-end solutions. The Panalpina Group operates a global network with some 500 offices in more than 80 countries, and employs around 15,000 people worldwide.We are looking to hire a Logistics Support, Business Process and Implementation Specialist to be responsible for supporting and implementing logistics opportunities with new and existing clients as well as continuous improvement and business process improvement activities in existing Panalpina operations. The person will work closely with the Country Heads of Logistics, local and regional logistics operations, and the Regional Head of Logistics.Responsibilities* Implementation Support :Support
Logistics process and IT migration design in conjunction with the Business Implementation team for implementation of new client engagements and business expansion with existing customers* Business Process Improvement / Continuous Process ImprovementSupport operations as needed in implementing and monitoring quality programs and continuous improvement methodologies to drive business process improvement activities* Operational “Fire Fighting” for Logistics Performance IssuesSupporting local operational stabilization activities
and to support internally or externally identified performance issues and develop base case and root cause analysisQualifications* Graduate degree required preferable in the field of Logistics or Industrial Engineering with specializationin Logistics, Lean or Project Management* Minimum 5 years of experience in the logistics industry* Minimum 3 years of Implementation or Quality Management experience* Experience with Logistics modeling or optimization tools* Six Sigma and Lean supply chain experience* Experience with Warehouse Management Systems and Logistics Operations Platforms* Broad end-to-end background in logistics and supply chain with core focus on contract logistics* Knowledge of electronic data interchange (EDI) and interface design* Project Management Certifications an advantageSkills and Competencies* Assertiveness* Self-motivated with ability to work independently and/or as part of a team* Ability to interact at all levels in an organization with strong inter-personal skills* Capable to make informed judgments and to generate practical, timely solutions* Ability to find pragmatic solutions by using decision making techniques* Willingness to involve stakeholders in decision making process, to get buy-in and to implement solutions* Ability to coordinate efforts/resources within and across boundaries to deliver goals* Ability to work with different cultures and to manage cross functional interfaces* Team player* Results oriented and places great emphasis on customer focus* Successful when working under pressure and tight timelinesLanguages* Fluent in English (written and spoken)* French, Russian, Portuguese advantageousSpecifics for Job / Environment* Knowledge of Supply Chain modeling, optimization, and design tools (ex: Logivations, CAPS, CAST, etc.)* Proficient in MS office platforms* Proficiency in Project Management tools* Knowledge of Logistics Operations Platforms, Distribution and Transit/Cross-Dock Warehouse Management Systems
